    <div class=3D"s-prose js-post-body" itemprop=3D"text">
<p>A case of recent personal experience:</p>

<p>I've been working on a card game myself (Bisca, a 2-player Portuguese ga=
me), and I've been getting good results using Monte Carlo methods, speciall=
y using the recent Information Set Monte Carlo Tree Search algorithm (ISMCT=
S, described with example source code in Python at <a href=3D"http://www.ai=
factory.co.uk/newsletter/2013_01_reduce_burden.htm" rel=3D"noreferrer">http=
://www.aifactory.co.uk/newsletter/2013_01_reduce_burden.htm</a>).</p>

<p>It plays reasonably well, with the ocasional incorrect move, just with t=
he knowledge of game rules. I'm currently trying to grok it, to be able to =
enhance it, as according to the information I've read about it (and its "pa=
rent" MCTS) it's possible to enhance its game play with heuristics (<a href=
=3D"http://www.orangehelicopter.com/ed/papers/aiide13.pdf" rel=3D"noreferre=
r">http://www.orangehelicopter.com/ed/papers/aiide13.pdf</a>) and opponent =
card inference.</p>
